    "shortDescription": "Elk are huge — males can weigh as much as four hundred and fifty kilograms and carry a rack of antlers wider than a person is tall. In autumn, males let out a haunting, echoing bugle call to challenge rivals and impress females. It's one of the most dramatic sounds in any forest. Fun fact: A male elk's antlers can grow as long as one and a half meters and weigh up to eighteen kilograms."
